text: Thanks for the response <@U16Q0J0E6>.  I look forward to consuming what you produce when you are able to produce it.  I do hope to call will be recorded, but anyway I think having up-to-date written materials that are hopefully accessible to mortals such as myself is a more important end goal.  As mentioned, I'm happy to provide feedback from the perspective of said mortal.  Thanks.

Not sure if this is the appropriate place or this, but I came across this in prep for the ID 2020 Workshop.  Lots of interesting relevant reads (and probably written by a few folks here). <https://github.com/WebOfTrustInfo/ID2020DesignWorkshop>

text: <@U0UFDAS91>: What are the dates/times for the bi-weekly Identity WG calls for June, so that IBM can get on the calendar to present updated slides at one of those?

<@U16Q0J0E6>: All meetings are listed now under <http://Hyperledger.org/community|Hyperledger.org/community> page under the Working Group Meetings list. The upcoming meetings are today, 1 Jun, 15 June, 29 June.

<@U14UG9CF8>: I’m hosting the ID2020DesignWorkshop and there is still a little more room if anyone in NYC area wants to participate. There a number of new topics papers posted at <https://github.com/WebOfTrustInfo/ID2020DesignWorkshop/tree/master/topics-and-advance-readings> in advance of this weekend.
